@startuml
' @id(SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD)
' @ref(USE-INIT-FORCE)
' @ref(USE-INIT-MIGRATE)
' @ref(USE-INIT-RALPH)
' @desc(SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD, "Objective flow of one `mdd init [--force]` invocation. The CLI (Commands::Init { force }) picks a conflict handler — always-Overwrite when --force, else the interactive prompt_init_conflict — and passes it to Project::init_with_conflict_handler. The engine: (1) creates any missing directories (including .mdd/ralph); (2) for each REGENERABLE file (docs, workflow skills incl. mdd-ralph, CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks, SessionStart hook, .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md) writes via write_text_if_missing(handler): create when missing, otherwise overwrite-or-skip per the handler (so --force overwrites, no-flag prompts); (3) for the SeededOnce file .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md runs write_text_create_if_missing (no handler): create from the starter template when missing, else skip — so it is never overwritten, not even by --force; (4) for each of the three STATE files runs write_yaml_create_or_migrate: create from default when missing, migrate when on_disk.version < current schema version, else skip. It returns InitReport { created, overwritten, migrated, skipped } which the CLI prints. Neither the SeededOnce branch nor the state branch consults the conflict handler, so --force can reach neither PLAN.md nor config/trace/approvals.")
' Objective sequence for cycle 0018 (force + migrate) and cycle 0022
' (the SeededOnce PLAN.md branch): one init invocation, three file
' classes — regenerable (handler-driven overwrite), seeded-once
' (create-if-missing, handler-independent), and accumulating state
' (create-or-forward-migrate, handler-independent).
title mdd init [--force] — regenerable overwrite vs state migration (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev
participant "mdd init [--force]\n(Commands::Init)" as Cli
participant "Project::init_with_\nconflict_handler" as Engine
participant "write_text_if_missing\n(regenerable)" as Text
participant "write_text_create_\nif_missing (seeded-once)" as Seed
participant "write_yaml_create_\nor_migrate (state)" as Yaml

Dev -> Cli : mdd init [--force]
alt force flag set
  Cli -> Cli : handler = always Overwrite
else no flag (default)
  Cli -> Cli : handler = prompt_init_conflict ([o/S])
end
Cli -> Engine : init_with_conflict_handler(handler)
Engine -> Engine : create missing directories

group regenerable files (docs, skills, blocks, hook)
  Engine -> Text : write_text_if_missing(handler)
  alt missing
    Text --> Engine : create
  else exists + handler=Overwrite
    Text --> Engine : overwrite
  else exists + handler=Skip
    Text --> Engine : skip
  end
end

group seeded-once file (.mdd/ralph/PLAN.md) — handler NOT consulted
  Engine -> Seed : write_text_create_if_missing(PLAN.md)
  alt missing
    Seed --> Engine : create from starter template
  else exists
    Seed --> Engine : skip (never overwritten, even by --force)
  end
end

group state files (config / trace / approvals) — handler NOT consulted
  Engine -> Yaml : create_or_migrate(default, current_version)
  alt missing
    Yaml --> Engine : create from default
  else on_disk.version < current
    Yaml --> Engine : migrate (parse->bump version->write)
  else on_disk.version >= current
    Yaml --> Engine : skip (idempotent / never downgrade)
  end
end

Engine --> Cli : InitReport { created, overwritten, migrated, skipped }
Cli --> Dev : print summary lines
@enduml
